SIMPLE: avale
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Avale
<hw>A*vale"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>avaler</ets> to descend, to let down. See
<er>Avalanche</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To cause to descend; to
lower; to let fall; to doff.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To bring low; to abase.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sir H. Wotton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(v. i.)</fld> <def>To descend; to fall; to
dismount.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And from their sweaty courses did <qex>avale</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Avant</ent>⟦br⟧
